cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses a methodology for performing machine learning and data analysis tasks on a specific target region of a large data set using semi-supervised eigenvectors of a graph Laplacian. This falls under the category of large-scale machine learning and data analysis, which is typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also provides examples of using the methodology for image analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between their results and recent machine learning algorithms that use global eigenvectors of the graph Laplacian, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
